
Deus, qui pópulo tuo ætérnæ salútis beátum <sr>N.</s> minístrum tribuísti: præsta, quæsumus; ut quem Doctórem vitæ habúimus in terris, intercessórem habére mereámur in cælis. Per Dóminum.
O God, who didst give blessed <sr>N.</s> to thy people to be a minister of eternal salvation; grant, we beseech thee, that we may deserve to have him for an intercessor in heaven whom we have had as a teacher of life on earth. Through our Lord.
